				\begin{document}$$Foxp{2^{S321X/+}}$$\end{document}Foxp2S321X/+ mice (6–8 weeks old) and wild-type littermate controls were placed on an accelerating rotarod (LE8200, Harvard apparatus) which increased rotation speed from 4 to 40 r.p.m. over a 5-min period. Mice were trained for five consecutive days, with five trials per day. Latency to fall (in seconds or RPM at fall) was scored, and mice were placed back in their home cage for 5 min between trials.
